HEADWORD: Samarskite
<hw>Sa*mar"skite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[After
<ets>Samarski</ets>, a Russian.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A rare
mineral having a velvet-black color and submetallic luster. It is a
niobate of uranium, iron, and the yttrium and cerium metals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

